82void qdbusDefaultThreadDebug(int action, int condition, QDBusConnectionPrivate *conn)
83{
84 qDBusDebug() << QThread::currentThread()
85 << "Qt D-Bus threading action" << action
86 << (condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforeLock ? "before lock" :
87 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterLock ? "after lock" :
88 condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforeUnlock ? "before unlock" :
89 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterUnlock ? "after unlock" :
90 condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforePost ? "before event posting" :
91 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterPost ? "after event posting" :
92 condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforeDeliver ? "before event delivery" :
93 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterDeliver ? "after event delivery" :
94 condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforeAcquire ? "before acquire" :
95 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterAcquire ? "after acquire" :
96 condition == QDBusLockerBase::BeforeRelease ? "before release" :
97 condition == QDBusLockerBase::AfterRelease ? "after release" :
98 "condition unknown")
99 << "in connection" << conn;
100}
101qdbusThreadDebugFunc qdbusThreadDebug = nullptr;

111static dbus_bool_t qDBusAddTimeout(DBusTimeout *timeout, void *data)
112{
113 Q_ASSERT(timeout);
114 Q_ASSERT(data);
115
116 // qDebug("addTimeout %d", q_dbus_timeout_get_interval(timeout));
117
118 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
119 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() == d->thread());
120
121 // we may get called from qDBusToggleTimeout
122 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!q_dbus_timeout_get_enabled(timeout)))
123 return false;
124
125 Q_ASSERT(d->timeouts.key(timeout, 0) == 0);
126
127 int timerId = d->startTimer(interval: q_dbus_timeout_get_interval(timeout));
128 Q_ASSERT_X(timerId, "QDBusConnection", "Failed to start a timer");
129 if (!timerId)
130 return false;
131
132 d->timeouts[timerId] = timeout;
133 return true;
134}

136static void qDBusRemoveTimeout(DBusTimeout *timeout, void *data)
137{
138 Q_ASSERT(timeout);
139 Q_ASSERT(data);
140
141 // qDebug("removeTimeout");
142
143 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
144 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() == d->thread());
145
146 QDBusConnectionPrivate::TimeoutHash::iterator it = d->timeouts.begin();
147 while (it != d->timeouts.end()) {
148 if (it.value() == timeout) {
149 d->killTimer(id: it.key());
150 it = d->timeouts.erase(it);
151 break;
152 } else {
153 ++it;
154 }
155 }
156}

169static dbus_bool_t qDBusAddWatch(DBusWatch *watch, void *data)
170{
171 Q_ASSERT(watch);
172 Q_ASSERT(data);
173
174 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
175 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() == d->thread());
176
177 int flags = q_dbus_watch_get_flags(watch);
178 int fd = q_dbus_watch_get_unix_fd(watch);
179
180 QDBusConnectionPrivate::Watcher watcher;
181
182 if (flags & DBUS_WATCH_READABLE) {
183 //qDebug("addReadWatch %d", fd);
184 watcher.watch = watch;
185 watcher.read = new QSocketNotifier(fd, QSocketNotifier::Read, d);
186 watcher.read->setEnabled(q_dbus_watch_get_enabled(watch));
187 d->connect(sender: watcher.read, signal: &QSocketNotifier::activated, receiver: d, slot: &QDBusConnectionPrivate::socketRead);
188 }
189 if (flags & DBUS_WATCH_WRITABLE) {
190 //qDebug("addWriteWatch %d", fd);
191 watcher.watch = watch;
192 watcher.write = new QSocketNotifier(fd, QSocketNotifier::Write, d);
193 watcher.write->setEnabled(q_dbus_watch_get_enabled(watch));
194 d->connect(sender: watcher.write, signal: &QSocketNotifier::activated, receiver: d, slot: &QDBusConnectionPrivate::socketWrite);
195 }
196 d->watchers.insert(key: fd, value: watcher);
197
198 return true;
199}

201static void qDBusRemoveWatch(DBusWatch *watch, void *data)
202{
203 Q_ASSERT(watch);
204 Q_ASSERT(data);
205
206 //qDebug("remove watch");
207
208 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
209 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() == d->thread());
210 int fd = q_dbus_watch_get_unix_fd(watch);
211
212 QDBusConnectionPrivate::WatcherHash::iterator i = d->watchers.find(key: fd);
213 while (i != d->watchers.end() && i.key() == fd) {
214 if (i.value().watch == watch) {
215 delete i.value().read;
216 delete i.value().write;
217 i = d->watchers.erase(it: i);
218 } else {
219 ++i;
220 }
221 }
222}

224static void qDBusToggleWatch(DBusWatch *watch, void *data)
225{
226 Q_ASSERT(watch);
227 Q_ASSERT(data);
228
229 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
230 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() == d->thread());
231 int fd = q_dbus_watch_get_unix_fd(watch);
232
233 QDBusConnectionPrivate::WatcherHash::iterator i = d->watchers.find(key: fd);
234 while (i != d->watchers.end() && i.key() == fd) {
235 if (i.value().watch == watch) {
236 bool enabled = q_dbus_watch_get_enabled(watch);
237 int flags = q_dbus_watch_get_flags(watch);
238
239 //qDebug("toggle watch %d to %d (write: %d, read: %d)", q_dbus_watch_get_fd(watch), enabled, flags & DBUS_WATCH_WRITABLE, flags & DBUS_WATCH_READABLE);
240
241 if (flags & DBUS_WATCH_READABLE && i.value().read)
242 i.value().read->setEnabled(enabled);
243 if (flags & DBUS_WATCH_WRITABLE && i.value().write)
244 i.value().write->setEnabled(enabled);
245 return;
246 }
247 ++i;
248 }
249}

260static void qDBusNewConnection(DBusServer *server, DBusConnection *connection, void *data)
261{
262 // ### We may want to separate the server from the QDBusConnectionPrivate
263 Q_ASSERT(server);
264 Q_UNUSED(server);
265 Q_ASSERT(connection);
266 Q_ASSERT(data);
267
268 if (!QDBusConnectionManager::instance())
269 return;
270
271 // keep the connection alive
272 q_dbus_connection_ref(connection);
273 QDBusConnectionPrivate *serverConnection = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
274
275 // allow anonymous authentication
276 if (serverConnection->anonymousAuthenticationAllowed)
277 q_dbus_connection_set_allow_anonymous(connection, value: true);
278
279 QDBusConnectionPrivate *newConnection = new QDBusConnectionPrivate(serverConnection->parent());
280 const auto locker = qt_scoped_lock(mutex&: QDBusConnectionManager::instance()->mutex);
281 QDBusConnectionManager::instance()->setConnection(name: "QDBusServer-"_L1 + QString::number(reinterpret_cast<qulonglong>(newConnection), base: 16), c: newConnection);
282 serverConnection->serverConnectionNames << newConnection->name;
283
284 // setPeer does the error handling for us
285 QDBusErrorInternal error;
286 newConnection->setPeer(connection, error);
287 newConnection->setDispatchEnabled(false);
288
289 // this is a queued connection and will resume in the QDBusServer's thread
290 emit serverConnection->newServerConnection(newConnection);
291
292 // we've disabled dispatching of events, so now we post an event to the
293 // QDBusServer's thread in order to enable it after the
294 // QDBusServer::newConnection() signal has been received by the
295 // application's code
296 newConnection->ref.ref();
297 QReadLocker serverLock(&serverConnection->lock);
298 QDBusConnectionDispatchEnabler *o = new QDBusConnectionDispatchEnabler(newConnection);
299 QTimer::singleShot(msec: 0, receiver: o, SLOT(execute()));
300 if (serverConnection->serverObject)
301 o->moveToThread(thread: serverConnection->serverObject->thread());
302}

312static QByteArray buildMatchRule(const QString &service,
313 const QString &objectPath, const QString &interface,
314 const QString &member, const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ArgMatchRules &argMatch, const QString & /*signature*/)
315{
316 QString result;
317 result += "type='signal',"_L1;
318 const auto keyValue = "%1='%2',"_L1;
319
320 if (!service.isEmpty())
321 result += keyValue.arg(args: "sender"_L1, args: service);
322 if (!objectPath.isEmpty())
323 result += keyValue.arg(args: "path"_L1, args: objectPath);
324 if (!interface.isEmpty())
325 result += keyValue.arg(args: "interface"_L1, args: interface);
326 if (!member.isEmpty())
327 result += keyValue.arg(args: "member"_L1, args: member);
328
329 // add the argument string-matching now
330 if (!argMatch.args.isEmpty()) {
331 const QString keyValue = "arg%1='%2',"_L1;
332 for (int i = 0; i < argMatch.args.size(); ++i)
333 if (!argMatch.args.at(i).isNull())
334 result += keyValue.arg(a: i).arg(a: argMatch.args.at(i));
335 }
336 if (!argMatch.arg0namespace.isEmpty()) {
337 result += "arg0namespace='%1',"_L1.arg(args: argMatch.arg0namespace);
338 }
339
340 result.chop(n: 1); // remove ending comma
341 return result.toLatin1();
342}

344static bool findObject(const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode *root,
345 const QString &fullpath, int &usedLength,
346 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode &result)
347{
348 if (!fullpath.compare(other: "/"_L1) && root->obj) {
349 usedLength = 1;
350 result = *root;
351 return root;
352 }
353 int start = 0;
354 int length = fullpath.size();
355 if (fullpath.at(i: 0) == u'/')
356 start = 1;
357
358 // walk the object tree
359 const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode *node = root;
360 while (start < length && node) {
361 if (node->flags & QDBusConnection::ExportChildObjects)
362 break;
363 if ((node->flags & QDBusConnectionPrivate::VirtualObject) && (node->flags & QDBusConnection::SubPath))
364 break;
365 int end = fullpath.indexOf(c: u'/', from: start);
366 end = (end == -1 ? length : end);
367 QStringView pathComponent = QStringView{fullpath}.mid(pos: start, n: end - start);
368
369 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode::DataList::ConstIterator it =
370 std::lower_bound(node->children.constBegin(), node->children.constEnd(), pathComponent);
371 if (it != node->children.constEnd() && it->name == pathComponent)
372 // match
373 node = &(*it);
374 else
375 node = nullptr;
376
377 start = end + 1;
378 }
379
380 // found our object
381 usedLength = (start > length ? length : start);
382 if (node) {
383 if (node->obj || !node->children.isEmpty())
384 result = *node;
385 else
386 // there really is no object here
387 // we're just looking at an unused space in the QList
388 node = nullptr;
389 }
390 return node;
391}

393static QObject *findChildObject(const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode *root,
394 const QString &fullpath, int start)
395{
396 int length = fullpath.size();
397
398 // any object in the tree can tell us to switch to its own object tree:
399 const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode *node = root;
400 if (node && node->flags & QDBusConnection::ExportChildObjects) {
401 QObject *obj = node->obj;
402
403 while (obj) {
404 if (start >= length)
405 // we're at the correct level
406 return obj;
407
408 int pos = fullpath.indexOf(c: u'/', from: start);
409 pos = (pos == -1 ? length : pos);
410 auto pathComponent = QStringView{fullpath}.mid(pos: start, n: pos - start);
411
412 const QObjectList children = obj->children();
413
414 // find a child with the proper name
415 QObject *next = nullptr;
416 QObjectList::ConstIterator it = children.constBegin();
417 QObjectList::ConstIterator end = children.constEnd();
418 for ( ; it != end; ++it)
419 if ((*it)->objectName() == pathComponent) {
420 next = *it;
421 break;
422 }
423
424 if (!next)
425 break;
426
427 obj = next;
428 start = pos + 1;
429 }
430 }
431
432 // object not found
433 return nullptr;
434}

436static QDBusConnectionPrivate::ArgMatchRules matchArgsForService(const QString &service, QDBusServiceWatcher::WatchMode mode)
437{
438 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ArgMatchRules matchArgs;
439 if (service.endsWith(c: u'*')) {
440 matchArgs.arg0namespace = service.chopped(n: 1);
441 matchArgs.args << QString();
442 }
443 else
444 matchArgs.args << service;
445
446 switch (mode) {
447 case QDBusServiceWatcher::WatchForOwnerChange:
448 break;
449
450 case QDBusServiceWatcher::WatchForRegistration:
451 matchArgs.args << QString::fromLatin1(str: "", size: 0);
452 break;
453
454 case QDBusServiceWatcher::WatchForUnregistration:
455 matchArgs.args << QString() << QString::fromLatin1(str: "", size: 0);
456 break;
457 }
458 return matchArgs;
459}

468QDBusSpyCallEvent::~QDBusSpyCallEvent()
469{
470 // Reinsert the message into the processing queue for the connection.
471 // This is done in the destructor so the message is reinserted even if
472 // QCoreApplication is destroyed.
473 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(const_cast<QObject *>(sender()));
474 qDBusDebug() << d << "message spies done for" << msg;
475 emit d->spyHooksFinished(msg);
476}

478void QDBusSpyCallEvent::placeMetaCall(QObject *)
479{
480 invokeSpyHooks(msg, hooks, hookCount);
481}

483inline void QDBusSpyCallEvent::invokeSpyHooks(const QDBusMessage &msg, const Hook *hooks, int hookCount)
484{
485 // call the spy hook list
486 for (int i = 0; i < hookCount; ++i)
487 hooks[i](msg);
488}

491static DBusHandlerResult
492qDBusSignalFilter(DBusConnection *connection, DBusMessage *message, void *data)
493{
494 Q_ASSERT(data);
495 Q_UNUSED(connection);
496 QDBusConnectionPrivate *d = static_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(data);
497 if (d->mode == QDBusConnectionPrivate::InvalidMode)
498 return DBUS_HANDLER_RESULT_NOT_YET_HANDLED;
499
500 QDBusMessage amsg = QDBusMessagePrivate::fromDBusMessage(dmsg: message, capabilities: d->connectionCapabilities());
501 qDBusDebug() << d << "got message (signal):" << amsg;
502
503 return d->handleMessage(msg: amsg) ?
504 DBUS_HANDLER_RESULT_HANDLED :
505 DBUS_HANDLER_RESULT_NOT_YET_HANDLED;
506}

508
509bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleMessage(const QDBusMessage &amsg)
510{
511 if (!ref.loadRelaxed())
512 return false;
513
514 // local message are always delivered, regardless of filtering
515 // or whether the dispatcher is enabled
516 bool isLocal = QDBusMessagePrivate::isLocal(msg: amsg);
517
518 if (!dispatchEnabled && !isLocal) {
519 // queue messages only, we'll handle them later
520 qDBusDebug() << this << "delivery is suspended";
521 pendingMessages << amsg;
522 return amsg.type() == QDBusMessage::MethodCallMessage;
523 }
524
525 switch (amsg.type()) {
526 case QDBusMessage::SignalMessage:
527 handleSignal(msg: amsg);
528 // if there are any other filters in this DBusConnection,
529 // let them see the signal too
530 return false;
531 case QDBusMessage::MethodCallMessage:
532 // run it through the spy filters (if any) before the regular processing:
533 // a) if it's a local message, we're in the caller's thread, so invoke the filter directly
534 // b) if it's an external message, post to the main thread
535 if (Q_UNLIKELY(qDBusSpyHookList.exists()) && qApp) {
536 const QDBusSpyHookList &list = *qDBusSpyHookList;
537 if (isLocal) {
538 Q_ASSERT(QThread::currentThread() != thread());
539 qDBusDebug() << this << "invoking message spies directly";
540 QDBusSpyCallEvent::invokeSpyHooks(msg: amsg, hooks: list.constData(), hookCount: list.size());
541 } else {
542 qDBusDebug() << this << "invoking message spies via event";
543 QCoreApplication::postEvent(qApp, event: new QDBusSpyCallEvent(this, QDBusConnection(this),
544 amsg, list.constData(), list.size()));
545
546 // we'll be called back, so return
547 return true;
548 }
549 }
550
551 handleObjectCall(message: amsg);
552 return true;
553 case QDBusMessage::ReplyMessage:
554 case QDBusMessage::ErrorMessage:
555 case QDBusMessage::InvalidMessage:
556 return false; // we don't handle those here
557 }
558
559 return false;
560}

562static void huntAndDestroy(QObject *needle, QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode &haystack)
563{
564 for (auto &node : haystack.children)
565 huntAndDestroy(needle, haystack&: node);
566
567 auto isInactive = [](const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode &node) { return !node.isActive(); };
568 haystack.children.removeIf(pred: isInactive);
569
570 if (needle == haystack.obj) {
571 haystack.obj = nullptr;
572 haystack.flags = 0;
573 }
574}
575
576static void huntAndUnregister(const QList<QStringView> &pathComponents, int i,
577 QDBusConnection::UnregisterMode mode,
578 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode *node)
579{
580 if (pathComponents.size() == i) {
581 // found it
582 node->obj = nullptr;
583 node->flags = 0;
584
585 if (mode == QDBusConnection::UnregisterTree) {
586 // clear the sub-tree as well
587 node->children.clear(); // can't disconnect the objects because we really don't know if they can
588 // be found somewhere else in the path too
589 }
590 } else {
591 // keep going
592 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode::DataList::Iterator end = node->children.end();
593 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode::DataList::Iterator it =
594 std::lower_bound(node->children.begin(), end, pathComponents.at(i));
595 if (it == end || it->name != pathComponents.at(i))
596 return; // node not found
597
598 huntAndUnregister(pathComponents, i: i + 1, mode, node: &(*it));
599 if (!it->isActive())
600 node->children.erase(pos: it);
601 }
602}

604static void huntAndEmit(DBusConnection *connection, DBusMessage *msg,
605 QObject *needle, const QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode &haystack,
606 bool isScriptable, bool isAdaptor, const QString &path = QString())
607{
608 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode::DataList::ConstIterator it = haystack.children.constBegin();
609 QDBusConnectionPrivate::ObjectTreeNode::DataList::ConstIterator end = haystack.children.constEnd();
610 for ( ; it != end; ++it) {
611 if (it->isActive())
612 huntAndEmit(connection, msg, needle, haystack: *it, isScriptable, isAdaptor, path: path + u'/' + it->name);
613 }
614
615 if (needle == haystack.obj) {
616 // is this a signal we should relay?
617 if (isAdaptor && (haystack.flags & QDBusConnection::ExportAdaptors) == 0)
618 return; // no: it comes from an adaptor and we're not exporting adaptors
619 else if (!isAdaptor) {
620 int mask = isScriptable
621 ? QDBusConnection::ExportScriptableSignals
622 : QDBusConnection::ExportNonScriptableSignals;
623 if ((haystack.flags & mask) == 0)
624 return; // signal was not exported
625 }
626
627 QByteArray p = path.toLatin1();
628 if (p.isEmpty())
629 p = "/";
630 qDBusDebug() << QThread::currentThread() << "emitting signal at" << p;
631 DBusMessage *msg2 = q_dbus_message_copy(message: msg);
632 q_dbus_message_set_path(message: msg2, object_path: p);
633 q_dbus_connection_send(connection, message: msg2, client_serial: nullptr);
634 q_dbus_message_unref(message: msg2);
635 }
636}

638static int findSlot(const QMetaObject *mo, const QByteArray &name, int flags,
639 const QString &signature_, QList<QMetaType> &metaTypes)
640{
641 QByteArray msgSignature = signature_.toLatin1();
642
643 for (int idx = mo->methodCount() - 1 ; idx >= QObject::staticMetaObject.methodCount(); --idx) {
644 QMetaMethod mm = mo->method(index: idx);
645
646 // check access:
647 if (mm.access() != QMetaMethod::Public)
648 continue;
649
650 // check type:
651 if (mm.methodType() != QMetaMethod::Slot && mm.methodType() != QMetaMethod::Method)
652 continue;
653
654 // check name:
655 if (mm.name() != name)
656 continue;
657
658 QMetaType returnType = mm.returnMetaType();
659 bool isAsync = qDBusCheckAsyncTag(tag: mm.tag());
660 bool isScriptable = mm.attributes() & QMetaMethod::Scriptable;
661
662 // consistency check:
663 if (isAsync && returnType.id() != QMetaType::Void)
664 continue;
665
666 QString errorMsg;
667 int inputCount = qDBusParametersForMethod(mm, metaTypes, errorMsg);
668 if (inputCount == -1)
669 continue; // problem parsing
670
671 metaTypes[0] = returnType;
672 bool hasMessage = false;
673 if (inputCount > 0 &&
674 metaTypes.at(i: inputCount) == QDBusMetaTypeId::message()) {
675 // "no input parameters" is allowed as long as the message meta type is there
676 hasMessage = true;
677 --inputCount;
678 }
679
680 // try to match the parameters
681 int i;
682 QByteArray reconstructedSignature;
683 for (i = 1; i <= inputCount; ++i) {
684 const char *typeSignature = QDBusMetaType::typeToSignature( type: metaTypes.at(i) );
685 if (!typeSignature)
686 break; // invalid
687
688 reconstructedSignature += typeSignature;
689 if (!msgSignature.startsWith(bv: reconstructedSignature))
690 break;
691 }
692
693 if (reconstructedSignature != msgSignature)
694 continue; // we didn't match them all
695
696 if (hasMessage)
697 ++i;
698
699 // make sure that the output parameters have signatures too
700 if (returnType.isValid() && returnType.id() != QMetaType::Void && QDBusMetaType::typeToSignature(type: returnType) == nullptr)
701 continue;
702
703 bool ok = true;
704 for (int j = i; ok && j < metaTypes.size(); ++j)
705 if (QDBusMetaType::typeToSignature(type: metaTypes.at(i)) == nullptr)
706 ok = false;
707 if (!ok)
708 continue;
709
710 // consistency check:
711 if (isAsync && metaTypes.size() > i + 1)
712 continue;
713
714 if (mm.methodType() == QMetaMethod::Slot) {
715 if (isScriptable && (flags & QDBusConnection::ExportScriptableSlots) == 0)
716 continue; // scriptable slots not exported
717 if (!isScriptable && (flags & QDBusConnection::ExportNonScriptableSlots) == 0)
718 continue; // non-scriptable slots not exported
719 } else {
720 if (isScriptable && (flags & QDBusConnection::ExportScriptableInvokables) == 0)
721 continue; // scriptable invokables not exported
722 if (!isScriptable && (flags & QDBusConnection::ExportNonScriptableInvokables) == 0)
723 continue; // non-scriptable invokables not exported
724 }
725
726 // if we got here, this slot matched
727 return idx;
728 }
729
730 // no slot matched
731 return -1;
732}

734/*!
735 \internal
736 Enables or disables the delivery of incoming method calls and signals. If
737 \a enable is true, this will also cause any queued, pending messages to be
738 delivered.
739 */
740void QDBusConnectionPrivate::setDispatchEnabled(bool enable)
741{
742 checkThread();
743 dispatchEnabled = enable;
744 if (enable)
745 emit dispatchStatusChanged();
746}

748static QDBusCallDeliveryEvent * const DIRECT_DELIVERY = (QDBusCallDeliveryEvent *)1;
749
750QDBusCallDeliveryEvent *QDBusConnectionPrivate::prepareReply(QDBusConnectionPrivate *target,
751 QObject *object, int idx,
752 const QList<QMetaType> &metaTypes,
753 const QDBusMessage &msg)
754{
755 Q_ASSERT(object);
756 Q_UNUSED(object);
757
758 int n = metaTypes.size() - 1;
759 if (metaTypes[n] == QDBusMetaTypeId::message())
760 --n;
761
762 if (msg.arguments().size() < n)
763 return nullptr; // too few arguments
764
765 // check that types match
766 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
767 if (metaTypes.at(i: i + 1) != msg.arguments().at(i).metaType() &&
768 msg.arguments().at(i).metaType() != QMetaType::fromType<QDBusArgument>())
769 return nullptr; // no match
770
771 // we can deliver
772 // prepare for the call
773 if (target == object)
774 return DIRECT_DELIVERY;
775 return new QDBusCallDeliveryEvent(QDBusConnection(target), idx, target, msg, metaTypes);
776}
777
778void QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateSignal(const QDBusConnectionPrivate::SignalHook& hook,
779 const QDBusMessage &msg)
780{
781 // This is called by QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleSignal to deliver a signal
782 // that was received from D-Bus
783 //
784 // Signals are delivered to slots if the parameters match
785 // Slots can have less parameters than there are on the message
786 // Slots can optionally have one final parameter that is a QDBusMessage
787 // Slots receive read-only copies of the message (i.e., pass by value or by const-ref)
788 QDBusCallDeliveryEvent *call = prepareReply(target: this, object: hook.obj, idx: hook.midx, metaTypes: hook.params, msg);
789 if (call == DIRECT_DELIVERY) {
790 // short-circuit delivery
791 Q_ASSERT(this == hook.obj);
792 deliverCall(object: this, flags: 0, msg, metaTypes: hook.params, slotIdx: hook.midx);
793 return;
794 }
795 if (call)
796 postEventToThread(action: ActivateSignalAction, target: hook.obj, event: call);
797}
798
799bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateCall(QObject* object, int flags, const QDBusMessage &msg)
800{
801 // This is called by QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleObjectCall to place a call
802 // to a slot on the object.
803 //
804 // The call is delivered to the first slot that matches the following conditions:
805 // - has the same name as the message's target member
806 // - ALL of the message's types are found in slot's parameter list
807 // - optionally has one more parameter of type QDBusMessage
808 // If none match, then the slot of the same name as the message target and with
809 // the first type of QDBusMessage is delivered.
810 //
811 // The D-Bus specification requires that all MethodCall messages be replied to, unless the
812 // caller specifically waived this requirement. This means that we inspect if the user slot
813 // generated a reply and, if it didn't, we will. Obviously, if the user slot doesn't take a
814 // QDBusMessage parameter, it cannot generate a reply.
815 //
816 // When a return message is generated, the slot's return type, if any, will be placed
817 // in the message's first position. If there are non-const reference parameters to the
818 // slot, they must appear at the end and will be placed in the subsequent message
819 // positions.
820
821 static const char cachePropertyName[] = "_qdbus_slotCache";
822
823 if (!object)
824 return false;
825
826 Q_ASSERT_X(QThread::currentThread() == object->thread(),
827 "QDBusConnection: internal threading error",
828 "function called for an object that is in another thread!!");
829
830 QDBusSlotCache slotCache =
831 qvariant_cast<QDBusSlotCache>(v: object->property(name: cachePropertyName));
832 QString cacheKey = msg.member(), signature = msg.signature();
833 if (!signature.isEmpty()) {
834 cacheKey.reserve(asize: cacheKey.size() + 1 + signature.size());
835 cacheKey += u'.';
836 cacheKey += signature;
837 }
838
839 QDBusSlotCache::Hash::ConstIterator cacheIt = slotCache.hash.constFind(key: cacheKey);
840 while (cacheIt != slotCache.hash.constEnd() && cacheIt->flags != flags &&
841 cacheIt.key() == cacheKey)
842 ++cacheIt;
843 if (cacheIt == slotCache.hash.constEnd() || cacheIt.key() != cacheKey)
844 {
845 // not cached, analyze the meta object
846 const QMetaObject *mo = object->metaObject();
847 QByteArray memberName = msg.member().toUtf8();
848
849 // find a slot that matches according to the rules above
850 QDBusSlotCache::Data slotData;
851 slotData.flags = flags;
852 slotData.slotIdx = ::findSlot(mo, name: memberName, flags, signature_: msg.signature(), metaTypes&: slotData.metaTypes);
853 if (slotData.slotIdx == -1) {
854 // ### this is where we want to add the connection as an arg too
855 // try with no parameters, but with a QDBusMessage
856 slotData.slotIdx = ::findSlot(mo, name: memberName, flags, signature_: QString(), metaTypes&: slotData.metaTypes);
857 if (slotData.metaTypes.size() != 2 ||
858 slotData.metaTypes.at(i: 1) != QDBusMetaTypeId::message()) {
859 // not found
860 // save the negative lookup
861 slotData.slotIdx = -1;
862 slotData.metaTypes.clear();
863 slotCache.hash.insert(key: cacheKey, value: slotData);
864 object->setProperty(name: cachePropertyName, value: QVariant::fromValue(value: slotCache));
865
866 qCWarning(dbusIntegration).nospace() << "Could not find slot " << mo->className()
867 << "::" << memberName.constData();
868 return false;
869 }
870 }
871
872 // save to the cache
873 slotCache.hash.insert(key: cacheKey, value: slotData);
874 object->setProperty(name: cachePropertyName, value: QVariant::fromValue(value: slotCache));
875
876 // found the slot to be called
877 deliverCall(object, flags, msg, metaTypes: slotData.metaTypes, slotIdx: slotData.slotIdx);
878 return true;
879 } else if (cacheIt->slotIdx == -1) {
880 // negative cache
881 return false;
882 } else {
883 // use the cache
884 deliverCall(object, flags, msg, metaTypes: cacheIt->metaTypes, slotIdx: cacheIt->slotIdx);
885 return true;
886 }
887 return false;
888}
889
890void QDBusConnectionPrivate::deliverCall(QObject *object, int /*flags*/, const QDBusMessage &msg,
891 const QList<QMetaType> &metaTypes, int slotIdx)
892{
893 Q_ASSERT_X(!object || QThread::currentThread() == object->thread(),
894 "QDBusConnection: internal threading error",
895 "function called for an object that is in another thread!!");
896
897 QVarLengthArray<void *, 10> params;
898 params.reserve(sz: metaTypes.size());
899
900 QVarLengthArray<QVariant, 10> auxParameters; // we cannot allow reallocation here, since we
901 auxParameters.reserve(sz: metaTypes.size()); // keep references to the entries
902
903 // let's create the parameter list
904
905 // first one is the return type -- add it below
906 params.append(t: nullptr);
907
908 // add the input parameters
909 int i;
910 int pCount = qMin(a: msg.arguments().size(), b: metaTypes.size() - 1);
911 for (i = 1; i <= pCount; ++i) {
912 auto id = metaTypes[i];
913 if (id == QDBusMetaTypeId::message())
914 break;
915
916 const QList<QVariant> args = msg.arguments();
917 const QVariant &arg = args.at(i: i - 1);
918 if (arg.metaType() == id)
919 // no conversion needed
920 params.append(t: const_cast<void *>(arg.constData()));
921 else if (arg.metaType() == QMetaType::fromType<QDBusArgument>()) {
922 // convert to what the function expects
923 auxParameters.append(t: QVariant(QMetaType(id)));
924
925 const QDBusArgument &in =
926 *reinterpret_cast<const QDBusArgument *>(arg.constData());
927 QVariant &out = auxParameters[auxParameters.size() - 1];
928
929 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!QDBusMetaType::demarshall(in, out.metaType(), out.data())))
930 qFatal(msg: "Internal error: demarshalling function for type '%s' (%d) failed!",
931 out.typeName(), out.metaType().id());
932
933 params.append(t: const_cast<void *>(out.constData()));
934 } else {
935 qFatal(msg: "Internal error: got invalid meta type %d (%s) "
936 "when trying to convert to meta type %d (%s)",
937 arg.metaType().id(), arg.metaType().name(),
938 id.id(), id.name());
939 }
940 }
941
942 if (metaTypes.size() > i && metaTypes[i] == QDBusMetaTypeId::message()) {
943 params.append(t: const_cast<void*>(static_cast<const void*>(&msg)));
944 ++i;
945 }
946
947 // output arguments
948 const int numMetaTypes = metaTypes.size();
949 QVariantList outputArgs;
950 if (metaTypes[0].id() != QMetaType::Void && metaTypes[0].isValid()) {
951 outputArgs.reserve(size: numMetaTypes - i + 1);
952 QVariant arg{QMetaType(metaTypes[0])};
953 outputArgs.append( t: arg );
954 params[0] = const_cast<void*>(outputArgs.at( i: outputArgs.size() - 1 ).constData());
955 } else {
956 outputArgs.reserve(size: numMetaTypes - i);
957 }
958
959 for ( ; i < numMetaTypes; ++i) {
960 QVariant arg{QMetaType(metaTypes[i])};
961 outputArgs.append( t: arg );
962 params.append(t: const_cast<void*>(outputArgs.at( i: outputArgs.size() - 1 ).constData()));
963 }
964
965 // make call:
966 bool fail;
967 if (!object) {
968 fail = true;
969 } else {
970 // FIXME: save the old sender!
971 QDBusContextPrivate context(QDBusConnection(this), msg);
972 QDBusContextPrivate *old = QDBusContextPrivate::set(obj: object, newContext: &context);
973
974 QPointer<QObject> ptr = object;
975 fail = object->qt_metacall(QMetaObject::InvokeMetaMethod,
976 slotIdx, params.data()) >= 0;
977 // the object might be deleted in the slot
978 if (!ptr.isNull())
979 QDBusContextPrivate::set(obj: object, newContext: old);
980 }
981
982 // do we create a reply? Only if the caller is waiting for a reply and one hasn't been sent
983 // yet.
984 if (msg.isReplyRequired() && !msg.isDelayedReply()) {
985 if (!fail) {
986 // normal reply
987 qDBusDebug() << this << "Automatically sending reply:" << outputArgs;
988 send(message: msg.createReply(arguments: outputArgs));
989 } else {
990 // generate internal error
991 qCWarning(dbusIntegration, "Internal error: Failed to deliver message");
992 send(message: msg.createErrorReply(type: QDBusError::InternalError, msg: "Failed to deliver message"_L1));
993 }
994 }
995
996 return;
997}

1045QDBusConnectionPrivate::~QDBusConnectionPrivate()
1046{
1047 if (thread() && thread() != QThread::currentThread())
1048 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
1049 "QDBusConnection(name=\"%s\")'s last reference in not in its creation thread! "
1050 "Timer and socket errors will follow and the program will probably crash",
1051 qPrintable(name));
1052
1053 auto lastMode = mode; // reset on connection close
1054 closeConnection();
1055 qDeleteAll(c: cachedMetaObjects);
1056
1057 if (lastMode == ClientMode || lastMode == PeerMode) {
1058 // the bus service object holds a reference back to us;
1059 // we need to destroy it before we finish destroying ourselves
1060 Q_ASSERT(ref.loadRelaxed() == 0);
1061 QObject *obj = (QObject *)busService;
1062 if (obj) {
1063 disconnect(sender: obj, signal: nullptr, receiver: this, member: nullptr);
1064 delete obj;
1065 }
1066 if (connection)
1067 q_dbus_connection_unref(connection: connection);
1068 connection = nullptr;
1069 } else if (lastMode == ServerMode) {
1070 if (server)
1071 q_dbus_server_unref(server: server);
1072 server = nullptr;
1073 }

1090void QDBusConnectionPrivate::closeConnection()
1091{
1092 QDBusWriteLocker locker(CloseConnectionAction, this);
1093 qDBusDebug() << this << "Disconnected";
1094 ConnectionMode oldMode = mode;
1095 mode = InvalidMode; // prevent reentrancy
1096 baseService.clear();
1097
1098 if (oldMode == ServerMode && server) {
1099 q_dbus_server_disconnect(server: server);
1100 q_dbus_server_free_data_slot(slot_p: &server_slot);
1101 }
1102
1103 if (oldMode == ClientMode || oldMode == PeerMode) {
1104 if (connection) {
1105 q_dbus_connection_close(connection: connection);
1106 // send the "close" message
1107 while (q_dbus_connection_dispatch(connection: connection) == DBUS_DISPATCH_DATA_REMAINS)
1108 ;
1109 }
1110 }
1111
1112 for (auto it = pendingCalls.begin(); it != pendingCalls.end(); ++it) {
1113 auto call = *it;
1114 if (!call->ref.deref()) {
1115 delete call;
1116 }
1117 }
1118 pendingCalls.clear();
1119
1120 // Disconnect all signals from signal hooks and from the object tree to
1121 // avoid QObject::destroyed being sent to dbus daemon thread which has
1122 // already quit. We need to make sure we disconnect exactly once per
1123 // object, because if we tried a second time, we might be hitting a
1124 // dangling pointer.
1125 QSet<QObject *> allObjects;
1126 collectAllObjects(haystack&: rootNode, set&: allObjects);
1127 SignalHookHash::const_iterator sit = signalHooks.constBegin();
1128 while (sit != signalHooks.constEnd()) {
1129 allObjects.insert(value: sit.value().obj);
1130 ++sit;
1131 }
1132
1133 // now disconnect ourselves
1134 QSet<QObject *>::const_iterator oit = allObjects.constBegin();
1135 while (oit != allObjects.constEnd()) {
1136 (*oit)->disconnect(receiver: this);
1137 ++oit;
1138 }
1139}

1143 while (!pendingCalls.isEmpty())

1145}

1175void QDBusConnectionPrivate::doDispatch()
1176{
1177 if (mode == ClientMode || mode == PeerMode) {
1178 while (q_dbus_connection_dispatch(connection: connection) == DBUS_DISPATCH_DATA_REMAINS) ;
1179 if (dispatchEnabled && !pendingMessages.isEmpty()) {
1180 // dispatch previously queued messages
1181 PendingMessageList::Iterator it = pendingMessages.begin();
1182 PendingMessageList::Iterator end = pendingMessages.end();
1183 for ( ; it != end; ++it) {
1184 qDBusDebug() << this << "dequeueing message" << *it;
1185 handleMessage(amsg: std::move(*it));
1186 }
1187 pendingMessages.clear();
1188 }
1189 }

1241void QDBusConnectionPrivate::relaySignal(QObject *obj, const QMetaObject *mo, int signalId,
1242 const QVariantList &args)
1243{
1244 QString interface = qDBusInterfaceFromMetaObject(mo);
1245
1246 QMetaMethod mm = mo->method(index: signalId);
1247 QByteArray memberName = mm.name();
1248
1249 // check if it's scriptable
1250 bool isScriptable = mm.attributes() & QMetaMethod::Scriptable;
1251 bool isAdaptor = false;
1252 for ( ; mo; mo = mo->superClass())
1253 if (mo == &QDBusAbstractAdaptor::staticMetaObject) {
1254 isAdaptor = true;
1255 break;
1256 }
1257
1258 checkThread();
1259 QDBusReadLocker locker(RelaySignalAction, this);
1260 QDBusMessage message = QDBusMessage::createSignal(path: "/"_L1, interface,
1261 name: QLatin1StringView(memberName));
1262 QDBusMessagePrivate::setParametersValidated(msg&: message, enable: true);
1263 message.setArguments(args);
1264 QDBusError error;
1265 DBusMessage *msg =
1266 QDBusMessagePrivate::toDBusMessage(message, capabilities: connectionCapabilities(), error: &error);
1267 if (!msg) {
1268 qCWarning(dbusIntegration, "QDBusConnection: Could not emit signal %s.%s: %s",
1269 qPrintable(interface), memberName.constData(), qPrintable(error.message()));
1270 lastError = error;
1271 return;
1272 }
1273
1274 //qDBusDebug() << "Emitting signal" << message;
1275 //qDBusDebug() << "for paths:";
1276 q_dbus_message_set_no_reply(message: msg, no_reply: true); // the reply would not be delivered to anything
1277 huntAndEmit(connection: connection, msg, needle: obj, haystack: rootNode, isScriptable, isAdaptor);
1278 q_dbus_message_unref(message: msg);
1279}

1281void QDBusConnectionPrivate::serviceOwnerChangedNoLock(const QString &name,
1282 const QString &oldOwner, const QString &newOwner)
1283{
1284 Q_UNUSED(oldOwner);
1285// QDBusWriteLocker locker(UpdateSignalHookOwnerAction, this);
1286 WatchedServicesHash::Iterator it = watchedServices.find(key: name);
1287 if (it == watchedServices.end())
1288 return;
1289 if (oldOwner != it->owner)
1290 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
1291 "QDBusConnection: name '%s' had owner '%s' but we thought it was '%s'",
1292 qPrintable(name), qPrintable(oldOwner), qPrintable(it->owner));
1293
1294 qDBusDebug() << this << "Updating name" << name << "from" << oldOwner << "to" << newOwner;
1295 it->owner = newOwner;

1298int QDBusConnectionPrivate::findSlot(QObject *obj, const QByteArray &normalizedName,
1299 QList<QMetaType> &params, QString &errorMsg)
1300{
1301 errorMsg.clear();
1302 int midx = obj->metaObject()->indexOfMethod(method: normalizedName);
1303 if (midx == -1)
1304 return -1;
1305
1306 int inputCount = qDBusParametersForMethod(mm: obj->metaObject()->method(index: midx), metaTypes&: params, errorMsg);
1307 if (inputCount == -1 || inputCount + 1 != params.size())
1308 return -1;
1309
1310 return midx;
1311}
1312
1313bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::prepareHook(QDBusConnectionPrivate::SignalHook &hook, QString &key,
1314 const QString &service,
1315 const QString &path, const QString &interface, const QString &name,
1316 const ArgMatchRules &argMatch,
1317 QObject *receiver, const char *signal, int minMIdx,
1318 bool buildSignature)
1319{
1320 QByteArray normalizedName = signal + 1;
1321 QString errorMsg;
1322 hook.midx = findSlot(obj: receiver, normalizedName: signal + 1, params&: hook.params, errorMsg);
1323 if (hook.midx == -1) {
1324 normalizedName = QMetaObject::normalizedSignature(method: signal + 1);
1325 hook.midx = findSlot(obj: receiver, normalizedName, params&: hook.params, errorMsg);
1326 }
1327 if (hook.midx < minMIdx) {
1328 return false;
1329 }
1330
1331 hook.service = service;
1332 hook.path = path;
1333 hook.obj = receiver;
1334 hook.argumentMatch = argMatch;
1335
1336 // build the D-Bus signal name and signature
1337 // This should not happen for QDBusConnection::connect, use buildSignature here, since
1338 // QDBusConnection::connect passes false and everything else uses true
1339 QString mname = name;
1340 if (buildSignature && mname.isNull()) {
1341 normalizedName.truncate(pos: normalizedName.indexOf(c: '('));
1342 mname = QString::fromUtf8(ba: normalizedName);
1343 }
1344 key = mname;
1345 key.reserve(asize: interface.size() + 1 + mname.size());
1346 key += u':';
1347 key += interface;
1348
1349 if (buildSignature) {
1350 hook.signature.clear();
1351 for (int i = 1; i < hook.params.size(); ++i)
1352 if (hook.params.at(i) != QDBusMetaTypeId::message())
1353 hook.signature += QLatin1StringView(QDBusMetaType::typeToSignature(type: hook.params.at(i)));
1354 }
1355
1356 hook.matchRule = buildMatchRule(service, objectPath: path, interface, member: mname, argMatch, hook.signature);
1357 return true; // connect to this signal
1358}

1360void QDBusConnectionPrivate::sendError(const QDBusMessage &msg, QDBusError::ErrorType code)
1361{
1362 if (code == QDBusError::UnknownMethod) {
1363 QString interfaceMsg;
1364 if (msg.interface().isEmpty())
1365 interfaceMsg = "any interface"_L1;
1366 else
1367 interfaceMsg = "interface '%1'"_L1.arg(args: msg.interface());
1368
1369 send(message: msg.createErrorReply(type: code, msg: "No such method '%1' in %2 at object path '%3' "
1370 "(signature '%4')"_L1
1371 .arg(args: msg.member(), args&: interfaceMsg, args: msg.path(), args: msg.signature())));
1372 } else if (code == QDBusError::UnknownInterface) {
1373 send(message: msg.createErrorReply(type: QDBusError::UnknownInterface,
1374 msg: "No such interface '%1' at object path '%2'"_L1
1375 .arg(args: msg.interface(), args: msg.path())));
1376 } else if (code == QDBusError::UnknownObject) {
1377 send(message: msg.createErrorReply(type: QDBusError::UnknownObject,
1378 msg: "No such object path '%1'"_L1.arg(args: msg.path())));
1379 }
1380}
1381
1382bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateInternalFilters(const ObjectTreeNode &node,
1383 const QDBusMessage &msg)
1384{
1385 // object may be null
1386 const QString interface = msg.interface();
1387
1388 if (interface.isEmpty() || interface == QDBusUtil::dbusInterfaceIntrospectable()) {
1389 if (msg.member() == "Introspect"_L1 && msg.signature().isEmpty()) {
1390 //qDebug() << "QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateInternalFilters introspect" << msg.d_ptr->msg;
1391 QDBusMessage reply = msg.createReply(argument: qDBusIntrospectObject(node, path: msg.path()));
1392 send(message: reply);
1393 return true;
1394 }
1395
1396 if (!interface.isEmpty()) {
1397 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownMethod);
1398 return true;
1399 }
1400 }
1401
1402 if (node.obj && (interface.isEmpty() ||
1403 interface == QDBusUtil::dbusInterfaceProperties())) {
1404 //qDebug() << "QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateInternalFilters properties" << msg.d_ptr->msg;
1405 if (msg.member() == "Get"_L1 && msg.signature() == "ss"_L1) {
1406 QDBusMessage reply = qDBusPropertyGet(node, msg);
1407 send(message: reply);
1408 return true;
1409 } else if (msg.member() == "Set"_L1 && msg.signature() == "ssv"_L1) {
1410 QDBusMessage reply = qDBusPropertySet(node, msg);
1411 send(message: reply);
1412 return true;
1413 } else if (msg.member() == "GetAll"_L1 && msg.signature() == "s"_L1) {
1414 QDBusMessage reply = qDBusPropertyGetAll(node, msg);
1415 send(message: reply);
1416 return true;
1417 }
1418
1419 if (!interface.isEmpty()) {
1420 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownMethod);
1421 return true;
1422 }
1423 }
1424
1425 return false;
1426}
1427
1428void QDBusConnectionPrivate::activateObject(ObjectTreeNode &node, const QDBusMessage &msg,
1429 int pathStartPos)
1430{
1431 // This is called by QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleObjectCall to place a call to a slot
1432 // on the object.
1433 //
1434 // The call is routed through the adaptor sub-objects if we have any
1435
1436 // object may be null
1437
1438 if (node.flags & QDBusConnectionPrivate::VirtualObject) {
1439 if (node.treeNode->handleMessage(message: msg, connection: q(connection: this))) {
1440 return;
1441 } else {
1442 if (activateInternalFilters(node, msg))
1443 return;
1444 }
1445 }
1446
1447 if (pathStartPos != msg.path().size()) {
1448 node.flags &= ~QDBusConnection::ExportAllSignals;
1449 node.obj = findChildObject(root: &node, fullpath: msg.path(), start: pathStartPos);
1450 if (!node.obj) {
1451 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownObject);
1452 return;
1453 }
1454 }
1455
1456 QDBusAdaptorConnector *connector;
1457 if (node.flags & QDBusConnection::ExportAdaptors &&
1458 (connector = qDBusFindAdaptorConnector(object: node.obj))) {
1459 int newflags = node.flags | QDBusConnection::ExportAllSlots;
1460
1461 if (msg.interface().isEmpty()) {
1462 // place the call in all interfaces
1463 // let the first one that handles it to work
1464 QDBusAdaptorConnector::AdaptorMap::ConstIterator it =
1465 connector->adaptors.constBegin();
1466 QDBusAdaptorConnector::AdaptorMap::ConstIterator end =
1467 connector->adaptors.constEnd();
1468
1469 for ( ; it != end; ++it)
1470 if (activateCall(object: it->adaptor, flags: newflags, msg))
1471 return;
1472 } else {
1473 // check if we have an interface matching the name that was asked:
1474 QDBusAdaptorConnector::AdaptorMap::ConstIterator it;
1475 it = std::lower_bound(connector->adaptors.constBegin(), connector->adaptors.constEnd(),
1476 msg.interface());
1477 if (it != connector->adaptors.constEnd() && msg.interface() == QLatin1StringView(it->interface)) {
1478 if (!activateCall(object: it->adaptor, flags: newflags, msg))
1479 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownMethod);
1480 return;
1481 }
1482 }
1483 }
1484
1485 // no adaptors matched or were exported
1486 // try our standard filters
1487 if (activateInternalFilters(node, msg))
1488 return; // internal filters have already run or an error has been sent
1489
1490 // try the object itself:
1491 if (node.flags & (QDBusConnection::ExportScriptableSlots|QDBusConnection::ExportNonScriptableSlots) ||
1492 node.flags & (QDBusConnection::ExportScriptableInvokables|QDBusConnection::ExportNonScriptableInvokables)) {
1493 bool interfaceFound = true;
1494 if (!msg.interface().isEmpty()) {
1495 if (!node.interfaceName.isEmpty())
1496 interfaceFound = msg.interface() == node.interfaceName;
1497 else
1498 interfaceFound = qDBusInterfaceInObject(obj: node.obj, interface_name: msg.interface());
1499 }
1500
1501 if (interfaceFound) {
1502 if (!activateCall(object: node.obj, flags: node.flags, msg))
1503 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownMethod);
1504 return;
1505 }
1506 }
1507
1508 // nothing matched, send an error code
1509 if (msg.interface().isEmpty())
1510 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownMethod);
1511 else
1512 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownInterface);
1513}
1514
1515void QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleObjectCall(const QDBusMessage &msg)
1516{
1517 // if the msg is external, we were called from inside doDispatch
1518 // that means the dispatchLock mutex is locked
1519 // must not call out to user code in that case
1520 //
1521 // however, if the message is internal, handleMessage was called directly
1522 // (user's thread) and no lock is in place. We can therefore call out to
1523 // user code, if necessary.
1524 ObjectTreeNode result;
1525 int usedLength;
1526 QThread *objThread = nullptr;
1527 QSemaphore sem;
1528 bool semWait;
1529
1530 {
1531 QDBusReadLocker locker(HandleObjectCallAction, this);
1532 if (!findObject(root: &rootNode, fullpath: msg.path(), usedLength, result)) {
1533 // qDebug("Call failed: no object found at %s", qPrintable(msg.path()));
1534 sendError(msg, code: QDBusError::UnknownObject);
1535 return;
1536 }
1537
1538 if (!result.obj) {
1539 // no object -> no threading issues
1540 // it's either going to be an error, or an internal filter
1541 activateObject(node&: result, msg, pathStartPos: usedLength);
1542 return;
1543 }
1544
1545 objThread = result.obj->thread();
1546 if (!objThread) {
1547 send(message: msg.createErrorReply(type: QDBusError::InternalError,
1548 msg: "Object '%1' (at path '%2')"
1549 " has no thread. Cannot deliver message."_L1
1550 .arg(args: result.obj->objectName(), args: msg.path())));
1551 return;
1552 }
1553
1554 if (!QDBusMessagePrivate::isLocal(msg)) {
1555 // external incoming message
1556 // post it and forget
1557 postEventToThread(action: HandleObjectCallPostEventAction, target: result.obj,
1558 event: new QDBusActivateObjectEvent(QDBusConnection(this), this, result,
1559 usedLength, msg));
1560 return;
1561 } else if (objThread != QThread::currentThread()) {
1562 // looped-back message, targeting another thread:
1563 // synchronize with it
1564 postEventToThread(action: HandleObjectCallPostEventAction, target: result.obj,
1565 event: new QDBusActivateObjectEvent(QDBusConnection(this), this, result,
1566 usedLength, msg, &sem));
1567 semWait = true;
1568 } else {
1569 // looped-back message, targeting current thread
1570 semWait = false;
1571 }
1572 } // release the lock
1573
1574 if (semWait)
1575 SEM_ACQUIRE(HandleObjectCallSemaphoreAction, sem);
1576 else
1577 activateObject(node&: result, msg, pathStartPos: usedLength);
1578}
1579
1580QDBusActivateObjectEvent::~QDBusActivateObjectEvent()
1581{
1582 if (!handled) {
1583 // we're being destroyed without delivering
1584 // it means the object was deleted between posting and delivering
1585 QDBusConnectionPrivate *that = QDBusConnectionPrivate::d(q: connection);
1586 that->sendError(msg: message, code: QDBusError::UnknownObject);
1587 }
1588
1589 // semaphore releasing happens in ~QMetaCallEvent
1590}
1591
1592void QDBusActivateObjectEvent::placeMetaCall(QObject *)
1593{
1594 QDBusConnectionPrivate *that = QDBusConnectionPrivate::d(q: connection);
1595
1596 QDBusLockerBase::reportThreadAction(HandleObjectCallPostEventAction,
1597 QDBusLockerBase::BeforeDeliver, that);
1598 that->activateObject(node, msg: message, pathStartPos);
1599 QDBusLockerBase::reportThreadAction(HandleObjectCallPostEventAction,
1600 QDBusLockerBase::AfterDeliver, that);
1601
1602 handled = true;
1603}

1605void QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleSignal(const QString &key, const QDBusMessage& msg)
1606{
1607 SignalHookHash::const_iterator it = signalHooks.constFind(key);
1608 SignalHookHash::const_iterator end = signalHooks.constEnd();
1609 //qDebug("looking for: %s", path.toLocal8Bit().constData());
1610 //qDBusDebug() << signalHooks.keys();
1611 for ( ; it != end && it.key() == key; ++it) {
1612 const SignalHook &hook = it.value();
1613 if (!hook.service.isEmpty()) {
1614 QString owner = watchedServices.value(key: hook.service, defaultValue: WatchedServiceData(hook.service)).owner;
1615 if (owner != msg.service())
1616 continue;
1617 }
1618 if (!hook.path.isEmpty() && hook.path != msg.path())
1619 continue;
1620 if (!hook.signature.isEmpty() && hook.signature != msg.signature())
1621 continue;
1622 if (hook.signature.isEmpty() && !hook.signature.isNull() && !msg.signature().isEmpty())
1623 continue;
1624 if (!hook.argumentMatch.args.isEmpty()) {
1625 const QVariantList arguments = msg.arguments();
1626 if (hook.argumentMatch.args.size() > arguments.size())
1627 continue;
1628
1629 bool matched = true;
1630 for (int i = 0; i < hook.argumentMatch.args.size(); ++i) {
1631 const QString &param = hook.argumentMatch.args.at(i);
1632 if (param.isNull())
1633 continue; // don't try to match against this
1634 if (param == arguments.at(i).toString())
1635 continue; // matched
1636 matched = false;
1637 break;
1638 }
1639 if (!matched)
1640 continue;
1641 }
1642 if (!hook.argumentMatch.arg0namespace.isEmpty()) {
1643 const QVariantList arguments = msg.arguments();
1644 if (arguments.size() < 1)
1645 continue;
1646 const QString param = arguments.at(i: 0).toString();
1647 const QStringView ns = hook.argumentMatch.arg0namespace;
1648 if (!param.startsWith(s: ns) || (param.size() != ns.size() && param[ns.size()] != u'.'))
1649 continue;
1650 }
1651 activateSignal(hook, msg);
1652 }
1653}
1654
1655void QDBusConnectionPrivate::handleSignal(const QDBusMessage& msg)
1656{
1657 // We call handlesignal(QString, QDBusMessage) three times:
1658 // one with member:interface
1659 // one with member:
1660 // one with :interface
1661 // This allows us to match signals with wildcards on member or interface
1662 // (but not both)
1663
1664 QString key = msg.member();
1665 key.reserve(asize: key.size() + 1 + msg.interface().size());
1666 key += u':';
1667 key += msg.interface();
1668
1669 QDBusReadLocker locker(HandleSignalAction, this);
1670 handleSignal(key, msg); // one try
1671
1672 key.truncate(pos: msg.member().size() + 1); // keep the ':'
1673 handleSignal(key, msg); // second try
1674
1675 key = u':';
1676 key += msg.interface();
1677 handleSignal(key, msg); // third try
1678}

1763static QDBusConnection::ConnectionCapabilities connectionCapabilies(DBusConnection *connection)
1764{
1765 QDBusConnection::ConnectionCapabilities result;
1766 typedef dbus_bool_t (*can_send_type_t)(DBusConnection *, int);
1767 static can_send_type_t can_send_type = nullptr;
1768
1769#if defined(QT_LINKED_LIBDBUS)
1770# if DBUS_VERSION-0 >= 0x010400
1771 can_send_type = dbus_connection_can_send_type;
1772# endif
1773#elif QT_CONFIG(library)
1774 // run-time check if the next functions are available
1775 can_send_type = (can_send_type_t)qdbus_resolve_conditionally("dbus_connection_can_send_type");
1776#endif

1778#ifndef DBUS_TYPE_UNIX_FD
1779# define DBUS_TYPE_UNIX_FD int('h')
1780#endif
1781 if (can_send_type && can_send_type(connection, DBUS_TYPE_UNIX_FD))

1793void QDBusConnectionPrivate::setConnection(DBusConnection *dbc, const QDBusErrorInternal &error)
1794{
1795 mode = ClientMode;
1796 if (!dbc) {
1797 handleError(error);
1798 return;
1799 }
1800
1801 connection = dbc;
1802
1803 const char *service = q_dbus_bus_get_unique_name(connection: connection);
1804 Q_ASSERT(service);
1805 baseService = QString::fromUtf8(utf8: service);
1806 // bus connections are already authenticated here because q_dbus_bus_register() has been called
1807 handleAuthentication();
1808
1809 q_dbus_connection_set_exit_on_disconnect(connection: connection, exit_on_disconnect: false);
1810 q_dbus_connection_set_watch_functions(connection: connection, add_function: qDBusAddWatch, remove_function: qDBusRemoveWatch,
1811 toggled_function: qDBusToggleWatch, data: this, free_data_function: nullptr);
1812 q_dbus_connection_set_timeout_functions(connection: connection, add_function: qDBusAddTimeout, remove_function: qDBusRemoveTimeout,
1813 toggled_function: qDBusToggleTimeout, data: this, free_data_function: nullptr);
1814 q_dbus_connection_set_dispatch_status_function(connection: connection, function: qDBusUpdateDispatchStatus, data: this, free_data_function: nullptr);
1815 q_dbus_connection_add_filter(connection: connection, function: qDBusSignalFilter, user_data: this, free_data_function: nullptr);
1816
1817 // Initialize the hooks for the NameAcquired and NameLost signals
1818 // we don't use connectSignal here because we don't need the rules to be sent to the bus
1819 // the bus will always send us these two signals
1820 SignalHook hook;
1821 hook.service = QDBusUtil::dbusService();
1822 hook.path.clear(); // no matching
1823 hook.obj = this;
1824 hook.params << QMetaType(QMetaType::Void) << QMetaType(QMetaType::QString); // both functions take a QString as parameter and return void
1825
1826 hook.midx = staticMetaObject.indexOfSlot(slot: "registerServiceNoLock(QString)");
1827 Q_ASSERT(hook.midx != -1);
1828 signalHooks.insert(key: "NameAcquired:" DBUS_INTERFACE_DBUS ""_L1, value: hook);
1829
1830 hook.midx = staticMetaObject.indexOfSlot(slot: "unregisterServiceNoLock(QString)");
1831 Q_ASSERT(hook.midx != -1);
1832 signalHooks.insert(key: "NameLost:" DBUS_INTERFACE_DBUS ""_L1, value: hook);
1833
1834 // And initialize the hook for the NameOwnerChanged signal;
1835 // we don't use connectSignal here because the rules are added by connectSignal on a per-need basis
1836 hook.params.clear();
1837 hook.params.reserve(size: 4);
1838 hook.params << QMetaType(QMetaType::Void) << QMetaType(QMetaType::QString) << QMetaType(QMetaType::QString) << QMetaType(QMetaType::QString);
1839 hook.midx = staticMetaObject.indexOfSlot(slot: "serviceOwnerChangedNoLock(QString,QString,QString)");
1840 Q_ASSERT(hook.midx != -1);
1841 signalHooks.insert(key: "NameOwnerChanged:" DBUS_INTERFACE_DBUS ""_L1, value: hook);
1842
1843 watchForDBusDisconnection();
1844
1845 qDBusDebug() << this << ": connected successfully";
1846
1847 // schedule a dispatch:
1848 QMetaObject::invokeMethod(obj: this, member: "doDispatch", c: Qt::QueuedConnection);
1849}

1860
1861void QDBusConnectionPrivate::processFinishedCall(QDBusPendingCallPrivate *call)
1862{
1863 QDBusConnectionPrivate *connection = const_cast<QDBusConnectionPrivate *>(call->connection);
1864
1865 auto locker = qt_unique_lock(mutex&: call->mutex);
1866
1867 connection->pendingCalls.removeOne(t: call);
1868
1869 QDBusMessage &msg = call->replyMessage;
1870 if (call->pending) {
1871 // when processFinishedCall is called and pending call is not completed,
1872 // it means we received disconnected signal from libdbus
1873 if (q_dbus_pending_call_get_completed(pending: call->pending)) {
1874 // decode the message
1875 DBusMessage *reply = q_dbus_pending_call_steal_reply(pending: call->pending);
1876 msg = QDBusMessagePrivate::fromDBusMessage(dmsg: reply, capabilities: connection->connectionCapabilities());
1877 q_dbus_message_unref(message: reply);
1878 } else {
1879 msg = QDBusMessage::createError(type: QDBusError::Disconnected, msg: QDBusUtil::disconnectedErrorMessage());
1880 }
1881 }
1882 qDBusDebug() << connection << "got message reply:" << msg;
1883
1884 // Check if the reply has the expected signature
1885 call->checkReceivedSignature();
1886
1887 if (!call->receiver.isNull() && call->methodIdx != -1 && msg.type() == QDBusMessage::ReplyMessage) {
1888 // Deliver the return values of a remote function call.
1889 //
1890 // There is only one connection and it is specified by idx
1891 // The slot must have the same parameter types that the message does
1892 // The slot may have less parameters than the message
1893 // The slot may optionally have one final parameter that is QDBusMessage
1894 // The slot receives read-only copies of the message (i.e., pass by value or by const-ref)
1895
1896 QDBusCallDeliveryEvent *e = prepareReply(target: connection, object: call->receiver, idx: call->methodIdx,
1897 metaTypes: call->metaTypes, msg);
1898 if (e)
1899 connection->postEventToThread(action: MessageResultReceivedAction, target: call->receiver, event: e);
1900 else
1901 qDBusDebug(msg: "Deliver failed!");
1902 }
1903
1904 if (call->pending) {
1905 q_dbus_pending_call_unref(pending: call->pending);
1906 call->pending = nullptr;
1907 }
1908
1909 // Are there any watchers?
1910 if (call->watcherHelper)
1911 call->watcherHelper->emitSignals(replyMessage: msg, sentMessage: call->sentMessage);
1912
1913 call->waitForFinishedCondition.wakeAll();
1914 locker.unlock();
1915
1916 if (msg.type() == QDBusMessage::ErrorMessage)
1917 emit connection->callWithCallbackFailed(error: QDBusError(msg), message: call->sentMessage);
1918
1919 if (!call->ref.deref())
1920 delete call;
1921}

1923bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::send(const QDBusMessage& message)
1924{
1925 if (QDBusMessagePrivate::isLocal(msg: message))
1926 return true; // don't send; the reply will be retrieved by the caller
1927 // through the d_ptr->localReply link
1928
1929 QDBusError error;
1930 DBusMessage *msg =
1931 QDBusMessagePrivate::toDBusMessage(message, capabilities: connectionCapabilities(), error: &error);
1932 if (!msg) {
1933 if (message.type() == QDBusMessage::MethodCallMessage)
1934 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
1935 "QDBusConnection: error: could not send message to service \"%s\" path "
1936 "\"%s\" interface \"%s\" member \"%s\": %s",
1937 qPrintable(message.service()), qPrintable(message.path()),
1938 qPrintable(message.interface()), qPrintable(message.member()),
1939 qPrintable(error.message()));
1940 else if (message.type() == QDBusMessage::SignalMessage)
1941 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
1942 "QDBusConnection: error: could not send signal to service \"%s\" path \"%s\" "
1943 "interface \"%s\" member \"%s\": %s",
1944 qPrintable(message.service()), qPrintable(message.path()),
1945 qPrintable(message.interface()), qPrintable(message.member()),
1946 qPrintable(error.message()));
1947 else
1948 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
1949 "QDBusConnection: error: could not send %s message to service \"%s\": %s",
1950 message.type() == QDBusMessage::ReplyMessage ? "reply"
1951 : message.type() == QDBusMessage::ErrorMessage ? "error"
1952 : "invalid",
1953 qPrintable(message.service()), qPrintable(error.message()));
1954 lastError = error;
1955 return false;
1956 }
1957
1958 q_dbus_message_set_no_reply(message: msg, no_reply: true); // the reply would not be delivered to anything
1959 qDBusDebug() << this << "sending message (no reply):" << message;
1960 emit messageNeedsSending(pcall: nullptr, msg);
1961 return true;
1962}

1964// small helper to note long running blocking dbus calls.
1965// these are generally a sign of fragile software (too long a call can either
1966// lead to bad user experience, if it's running on the GUI thread for instance)
1967// or break completely under load (hitting the call timeout).
1968//
1969// as a result, this is something we want to watch for.
1970class QDBusBlockingCallWatcher
1971{
1972public:
1973 QDBusBlockingCallWatcher(const QDBusMessage &message)
1974 : m_message(message), m_maxCallTimeoutMs(0)
1975 {
1976#if defined(QT_NO_DEBUG)
1977 // when in a release build, we default these to off.
1978 // this means that we only affect code that explicitly enables the warning.
1979 Q_CONSTINIT static int mainThreadWarningAmount = -1;
1980 Q_CONSTINIT static int otherThreadWarningAmount = -1;
1981#else
1982 Q_CONSTINIT static int mainThreadWarningAmount = 200;
1983 Q_CONSTINIT static int otherThreadWarningAmount = 500;
1984#endif
1985 Q_CONSTINIT static bool initializedAmounts = false;
1986 Q_CONSTINIT static QBasicMutex initializeMutex;
1987 auto locker = qt_unique_lock(mutex&: initializeMutex);
1988
1989 if (!initializedAmounts) {
1990 int tmp = 0;
1991 QByteArray env;
1992 bool ok = true;
1993
1994 env = qgetenv(varName: "Q_DBUS_BLOCKING_CALL_MAIN_THREAD_WARNING_MS");
1995 if (!env.isEmpty()) {
1996 tmp = env.toInt(ok: &ok);
1997 if (ok)
1998 mainThreadWarningAmount = tmp;
1999 else
2000 qCWarning(
2001 dbusIntegration,
2002 "QDBusBlockingCallWatcher: Q_DBUS_BLOCKING_CALL_MAIN_THREAD_WARNING_MS "
2003 "must be an integer; value ignored");
2004 }
2005
2006 env = qgetenv(varName: "Q_DBUS_BLOCKING_CALL_OTHER_THREAD_WARNING_MS");
2007 if (!env.isEmpty()) {
2008 tmp = env.toInt(ok: &ok);
2009 if (ok)
2010 otherThreadWarningAmount = tmp;
2011 else
2012 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
2013 "QDBusBlockingCallWatcher: "
2014 "Q_DBUS_BLOCKING_CALL_OTHER_THREAD_WARNING_MS must be an integer; "
2015 "value ignored");
2016 }
2017
2018 initializedAmounts = true;
2019 }
2020
2021 locker.unlock();
2022
2023 // if this call is running on the main thread, we have a much lower
2024 // tolerance for delay because any long-term delay will wreck user
2025 // interactivity.
2026 if (qApp && qApp->thread() == QThread::currentThread())
2027 m_maxCallTimeoutMs = mainThreadWarningAmount;
2028 else
2029 m_maxCallTimeoutMs = otherThreadWarningAmount;
2030
2031 m_callTimer.start();
2032 }
2033
2034 ~QDBusBlockingCallWatcher()
2035 {
2036 if (m_maxCallTimeoutMs < 0)
2037 return; // disabled
2038
2039 if (m_callTimer.elapsed() >= m_maxCallTimeoutMs) {
2040 qCWarning(
2041 dbusIntegration,
2042 "QDBusConnection: warning: blocking call took a long time (%d ms, max for this "
2043 "thread is %d ms) to service \"%s\" path \"%s\" interface \"%s\" member \"%s\"",
2044 int(m_callTimer.elapsed()), m_maxCallTimeoutMs, qPrintable(m_message.service()),
2045 qPrintable(m_message.path()), qPrintable(m_message.interface()),
2046 qPrintable(m_message.member()));
2047 }
2048 }
2049
2050private:
2051 QDBusMessage m_message;
2052 int m_maxCallTimeoutMs;
2053 QElapsedTimer m_callTimer;
2054};

2057QDBusMessage QDBusConnectionPrivate::sendWithReply(const QDBusMessage &message,
2058 int sendMode, int timeout)
2059{
2060 QDBusBlockingCallWatcher watcher(message);
2061
2062 QDBusPendingCallPrivate *pcall = sendWithReplyAsync(message, receiver: nullptr, returnMethod: nullptr, errorMethod: nullptr, timeout);
2063 Q_ASSERT(pcall);

2124QDBusPendingCallPrivate *QDBusConnectionPrivate::sendWithReplyAsync(const QDBusMessage &message,
2125 QObject *receiver, const char *returnMethod,
2126 const char *errorMethod, int timeout)
2127{
2128 QDBusPendingCallPrivate *pcall = new QDBusPendingCallPrivate(message, this);
2129 bool isLoopback;
2130 if ((isLoopback = isServiceRegisteredByThread(serviceName: message.service()))) {
2131 // special case for local calls
2132 pcall->replyMessage = sendWithReplyLocal(message);
2133 }
2134
2135 if (receiver && returnMethod)
2136 pcall->setReplyCallback(target: receiver, member: returnMethod);
2137
2138 if (errorMethod) {
2139 pcall->watcherHelper = new QDBusPendingCallWatcherHelper;
2140 connect(sender: pcall->watcherHelper, SIGNAL(error(QDBusError,QDBusMessage)), receiver, member: errorMethod,
2141 Qt::QueuedConnection);
2142 pcall->watcherHelper->moveToThread(thread: thread());
2143 }
2144
2145 if ((receiver && returnMethod) || errorMethod) {
2146 // no one waiting, will delete pcall in processFinishedCall()
2147 pcall->ref.storeRelaxed(newValue: 1);
2148 } else {
2149 // set double ref to prevent race between processFinishedCall() and ref counting
2150 // by QDBusPendingCall::QExplicitlySharedDataPointer<QDBusPendingCallPrivate>
2151 pcall->ref.storeRelaxed(newValue: 2);
2152 }
2153
2154 if (isLoopback) {
2155 // a loopback call
2156 processFinishedCall(call: pcall);
2157 return pcall;
2158 }
2159
2160 QDBusError error;
2161 DBusMessage *msg =
2162 QDBusMessagePrivate::toDBusMessage(message, capabilities: connectionCapabilities(), error: &error);
2163 if (!msg) {
2164 qCWarning(dbusIntegration,
2165 "QDBusConnection: error: could not send message to service \"%s\" path \"%s\" "
2166 "interface \"%s\" member \"%s\": %s",
2167 qPrintable(message.service()), qPrintable(message.path()),
2168 qPrintable(message.interface()), qPrintable(message.member()),
2169 qPrintable(error.message()));
2170 pcall->replyMessage = QDBusMessage::createError(err: error);
2171 lastError = error;
2172 processFinishedCall(call: pcall);
2173 } else {
2174 qDBusDebug() << this << "sending message:" << message;
2175 emit messageNeedsSending(pcall, msg, timeout);
2176 }
2177 return pcall;
2178}

2180void QDBusConnectionPrivate::sendInternal(QDBusPendingCallPrivate *pcall, void *message, int timeout)
2181{
2182 QDBusError error;
2183 DBusPendingCall *pending = nullptr;
2184 DBusMessage *msg = static_cast<DBusMessage *>(message);
2185 bool isNoReply = !pcall;
2186 Q_ASSERT(isNoReply == !!q_dbus_message_get_no_reply(msg));
2187
2188 checkThread();
2189
2190 if (isNoReply && q_dbus_connection_send(connection: connection, message: msg, client_serial: nullptr)) {
2191 // success
2192 } else if (!isNoReply && q_dbus_connection_send_with_reply(connection: connection, message: msg, pending_return: &pending, timeout_milliseconds: timeout)) {
2193 if (pending) {
2194 q_dbus_message_unref(message: msg);
2195
2196 pcall->pending = pending;
2197 q_dbus_pending_call_set_notify(pending, function: qDBusResultReceived, user_data: pcall, free_user_data: nullptr);
2198
2199 // DBus won't notify us when a peer disconnects or server terminates so we need to track these ourselves
2200 if (mode == QDBusConnectionPrivate::PeerMode || mode == QDBusConnectionPrivate::ClientMode)
2201 pendingCalls.append(t: pcall);
2202
2203 return;
2204 } else {
2205 // we're probably disconnected at this point
2206 lastError = error = QDBusError(QDBusError::Disconnected, QDBusUtil::disconnectedErrorMessage());
2207 }
2208 } else {
2209 lastError = error = QDBusError(QDBusError::NoMemory, QStringLiteral("Out of memory"));
2210 }
2211
2212 q_dbus_message_unref(message: msg);
2213 if (pcall) {
2214 pcall->replyMessage = QDBusMessage::createError(err: error);
2215 processFinishedCall(call: pcall);
2216 }
2217}

2446 i = 1;
2447 }

2449 huntAndUnregister(pathComponents, i, mode, node);

2499bool QDBusConnectionPrivate::shouldWatchService(const QString &service)
2500{
2501 // we don't have to watch anything in peer mode
2502 if (mode != ClientMode)
2503 return false;
2504 // we don't have to watch wildcard services (empty strings)
2505 if (service.isEmpty())
2506 return false;
2507 // we don't have to watch the bus driver
2508 if (service == QDBusUtil::dbusService())
2509 return false;
2510 return true;
2511}

2563QString QDBusConnectionPrivate::getNameOwnerNoCache(const QString &serviceName)
2564{
2565 QDBusMessage msg = QDBusMessage::createMethodCall(destination: QDBusUtil::dbusService(),
2566 path: QDBusUtil::dbusPath(), interface: QDBusUtil::dbusInterface(),
2567 QStringLiteral("GetNameOwner"));
2568 QDBusMessagePrivate::setParametersValidated(msg, enable: true);
2569 msg << serviceName;
2570
2571 QDBusPendingCallPrivate *pcall = sendWithReplyAsync(message: msg, receiver: nullptr, returnMethod: nullptr, errorMethod: nullptr);
2572 if (thread() == QThread::currentThread()) {
2573 // this function may be called in our own thread and
2574 // QDBusPendingCallPrivate::waitForFinished() would deadlock there
2575 q_dbus_pending_call_block(pending: pcall->pending);
2576 }
2577 pcall->waitForFinished();
2578 msg = pcall->replyMessage;
2579
2580 if (!pcall->ref.deref())
2581 delete pcall;
2582
2583 if (msg.type() == QDBusMessage::ReplyMessage)
2584 return msg.arguments().at(i: 0).toString();
2585 return QString();

2588QDBusMetaObject *
2589QDBusConnectionPrivate::findMetaObject(const QString &service, const QString &path,
2590 const QString &interface, QDBusError &error)
2591{
2592 // service must be a unique connection name
2593 if (!interface.isEmpty()) {
2594 QDBusReadLocker locker(FindMetaObject1Action, this);
2595 QDBusMetaObject *mo = cachedMetaObjects.value(key: interface, defaultValue: nullptr);
2596 if (mo)
2597 return mo;
2598 }
2599 if (path.isEmpty()) {
2600 error = QDBusError(QDBusError::InvalidObjectPath, "Object path cannot be empty"_L1);
2601 lastError = error;
2602 return nullptr;
2603 }
2604
2605 // introspect the target object
2606 QDBusMessage msg = QDBusMessage::createMethodCall(destination: service, path,
2607 interface: QDBusUtil::dbusInterfaceIntrospectable(),
2608 QStringLiteral("Introspect"));
2609 QDBusMessagePrivate::setParametersValidated(msg, enable: true);
2610
2611 QDBusMessage reply = sendWithReply(message: msg, sendMode: QDBus::Block);
2612
2613 // it doesn't exist yet, we have to create it
2614 QDBusWriteLocker locker(FindMetaObject2Action, this);
2615 QDBusMetaObject *mo = nullptr;
2616 if (!interface.isEmpty())
2617 mo = cachedMetaObjects.value(key: interface, defaultValue: nullptr);
2618 if (mo)
2619 // maybe it got created when we switched from read to write lock
2620 return mo;
2621
2622 QString xml;
2623 if (reply.type() == QDBusMessage::ReplyMessage) {
2624 if (reply.signature() == "s"_L1)
2625 // fetch the XML description
2626 xml = reply.arguments().at(i: 0).toString();
2627 } else {
2628 error = QDBusError(reply);
2629 lastError = error;
2630 if (reply.type() != QDBusMessage::ErrorMessage || error.type() != QDBusError::UnknownMethod)
2631 return nullptr; // error
2632 }
2633
2634 // release the lock and return
2635 QDBusMetaObject *result = QDBusMetaObject::createMetaObject(interface, xml,
2636 map&: cachedMetaObjects, error);
2637 lastError = error;
2638 return result;
2639}
